Decentralized Data Provenance L1
Overview

Decentralized Data Provenance L1 is a blockchain infrastructure designed to track the origin, history, and integrity of data across digital systems. It enables transparent verification of how datasets are created, modified, and shared.

Features

Immutable data origin records

Tamper-proof data history tracking

Dataset ownership verification

Cross-platform data integrity validation

Transparent audit trails

Architecture
Data Registry

Stores metadata describing datasets and their origin.

Provenance Tracking Engine

Records the lifecycle and transformation history of datasets.

Verification Layer

Validates authenticity through cryptographic proofs.

Integration APIs

Allows integration with analytics tools and data platforms.

Use Cases

AI dataset verification

Research data authenticity

Enterprise data compliance

Data marketplace transparency
